Script to build OpenSSL for iPhone device and simulator platform
Tested against:
	iPhone SDK 3.1.2 and 3.1.3
	OpenSSL 0.9.8n

Place openssl-0.9.8n.tar.gz in this directory, then:

	bash Build-OpenSSL.sh

library will be ready in newly created 'dist' directory.

I refered following blog page:
	Tutorial: How To Compile OpenSSL for the iPhone (1st Jan, 2009)
	http://www.therareair.com/2009/01/01/tutorial-how-to-compile-openssl-for-the-iphone/
